dc:description: Green. Base and fragment of side, blown into tripartite mould. Base flat, sides vertical at first, and then spreading out into bulb where the pattern begins. Honeycomb pattern of horizontal rows of hexagonal hollows in quincunx formation. Twenty-six hollows in the bottom row on each fragment. Identical and perhaps from same mould as 6088. No weathering. Very bubbly.
